detail_description: Café Matisse, a Bahamian-style Italian restaurant, is housed in a 19th-century colonial mansion behind Parliament Square. The interior boasts French decor and walls adorned with prints of the eponymous artist. The menu offers modern dishes like veal Calamarata pasta, rack of lamb with mint crust, and mahi-mahi with heirloom vegetables.
name: Café Matisse

detail_description: Graycliff Restaurant, located in the renowned Graycliff Hotel, is a celebrated dining destination that has attracted the likes of Beyoncé and Jay-Z. One of its most notable features is the award-winning wine cellar, boasting an impressive collection of 275,000 bottles from 20 different countries. The restaurant offers a sophisticated ambiance with live music and hand-rolled cigars in the lounge before guests move to the garden patio for an exquisite dining experience paired with an extensive selection of wines.
name: Graycliff Restaurant

excerpt: Seafood-focused menu with a local twist by a renowned chef, in an upscale hotel restaurant.
detail_description: Dune is an upscale restaurant located at The Ocean Club, A Four Seasons Resort on Paradise Island. It offers a seafood-focused menu with a local twist, crafted by renowned chef Jean-Georges Vongerichten. The restaurant's British colonial-style setting on Cabbage Beach provides stunning ocean views and a menu that combines local ingredients with French and Asian culinary influences.
name: Dune
address: Paradise Island, One Ocean Drive, Nassau, Bahamas

detail_description: Athena Cafe & Bar is a family-owned restaurant located on Bay Street since 1996. It has become a popular spot for both locals and visitors, offering Mediterranean food with Greek and Bahamian influences. The restaurant is known for its gluten-free options and is a favorite lunch spot for downtown workers and savvy cruisers. Guests can enjoy their meals on the second floor or balcony while taking in views of Nassau's downtown area.
name: Athena Cafe & Bar

detail_description: Located on Cable Beach, Meze Grill is a sophisticated Mediterranean restaurant offering a menu that combines seafood and meats in a refined yet relaxed atmosphere. The chic dining space features elegant decor with soft lighting, creating an intimate ambiance. The menu includes classic Mediterranean dishes such as fresh seafood, prime meats, imported pasta, and organic salads and vegetables. Guests can also enjoy a selection of fine wines from around the world, craft beers, and handcrafted cocktails.
name: Meze Grill

detail_description: Café Martinique is a sophisticated dining spot located in the Marina Village at the Atlantis Resort. The restaurant exudes an old-world charm with its vaulted ceilings and soft lighting, offering an intimate and elegant atmosphere. Accessible via a grand staircase or a unique wrought-iron bird-cage elevator, this fine dining establishment by Jean-Georges Vongerichten features a menu of French cuisine infused with tropical flavors and local ingredients.
name: Café Martinique
address: One Casino Drive Suite 4, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Sapodilla Estate is home to the renowned fine dining establishment, Sapodilla. The restaurant offers exceptional Bahamian cuisine and top-notch service in a beautiful setting. With floor-to-ceiling windows providing stunning garden views and soothing island-style interiors, diners are treated to a feast for the senses. The chefs at Sapodilla use fresh, locally sourced ingredients to create dishes that showcase the flavors of the Bahamas.
name: Sapodilla Estate

detail_description: Nestled just outside the upscale Lyford Cay community, Island Brothers Cie is a delightful French café and restaurant that offers an unexpected culinary experience in New Providence. This charming brasserie combines traditional French dining with tropical flair, making it a haven for food enthusiasts seeking something special. The family-run establishment serves up a delectable array of dishes, including their renowned Wagyu bavette paired with crispy pomme frites.
name: Island Brothers Cie

detail_description: Located in Nassau, Kyma Seafood Grill is a sophisticated restaurant offering a fusion of Greek and Latin flavors. The upscale ambiance and expansive menu make it an ideal choice for various occasions, from romantic date nights to special celebrations. With chic decor and attentive service, this establishment is popular among seafood enthusiasts. Menu highlights include the crowd-pleasing gyros and the must-try grilled snapper. It's recommended to make reservations due to its popularity.
name: Kyma Seafood Grill

detail_description: The New Duff is a must-visit spot, located about a 30-minute walk from the port. Despite the weather conditions, visitors found it worth the effort. The jerk chicken bun was particularly praised for its well-balanced spice and fresh veggies. The guava duff and banana duff were also highlights, with authentic fruit flavors that weren't overpowered by sweetness. Upon entering, guests were greeted by the delightful aroma of freshly baked bread.
name: The New Duff

detail_description: The Poop Deck at Sandyport is a renowned seafood restaurant and bar in Nassau, serving locals and visitors since 1972. It offers Bahamian-style seafood with stunning views of Nassau Harbour from its upper deck bar. The restaurant's unobstructed views of turquoise waters make it a popular choice for dining. Guests can enjoy dishes like cracked conch, fritters, and the highly recommended conch chowder served with johnny cake.
name: The Poop Deck at Sandyport

detail_description: Nobu, the internationally renowned restaurant chain by chef Nobu Matsuhisa, has established its presence in major cities worldwide. The Atlantis location mirrors the elegance and modern design of its counterparts, offering a diverse menu featuring sushi, sashimi, steaks, tempura, and various Japanese dishes. In Nassau at Atlantis Bahamas, Nobu provides an ultra-luxe dining experience with a fusion of Japanese and Peruvian influences.
name: Nobu
address: One Casino Drive, Suite 13, Paradise Island, Bahamas

excerpt: Relaxed, family-friendly restaurant serving a menu of homestyle Southern Italian meals.
detail_description: Carmine's is a delightful, family-friendly Italian restaurant that brings the essence of Southern Italy to life with its generous portions and warm atmosphere. Perfect for small groups, this eatery serves up hearty dishes in family-style servings, making it an ideal spot for sharing. The menu features a variety of appetizers, entrees, and desserts designed to satisfy even the hungriest diners.
name: Carmine's
address: One Casino Drive Suite 2, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Arawak Cay, also known as "The Fish Fry," is a vibrant dining area in Nassau, Bahamas. It features a colorful row of Bahamian restaurants and food stands offering a variety of local dishes such as conch salad, scorched conch, conch fritters, cracked conch, and conch chowder.
name: The Fish Fry

detail_description: Mogano by Giorgio Locatelli is a culinary gem that embraces simplicity while striving for perfection. This enchanting restaurant offers a delightful journey through the vibrant flavors of Thailand, Vietnam, and Indonesia. Guests can choose to dine in the elegant main dining room, at an intimate 8-seat sushi bar, or on the terrace with stunning waterside views that set a romantic ambiance.
name: Mogano by Giorgio Locatelli
address: Mahogany Hill Western Rd, Nassau, Bahamas

detail_description: Lukka Kairi Waterfront Bar & Grill is a vibrant seafront eatery located above Downtown Nassau's harborfront, offering a perfect spot to enjoy refreshing cocktails and innovative Bahamian cuisine. Since 2015, this modern restaurant has been serving up a mix of classic Bahamian dishes and contemporary creations.
name: Lukka Kairi Waterfront Bar & Grill

detail_description: JWB is an oceanside steak and seafood restaurant that offers a unique dining experience with its beautiful selections and settings. It features private upscale dining rooms, making it perfect for intimate gatherings and celebrations. Visitors have praised the restaurant for its great food and exceptional service, with particular mention of standout staff members like Phillip and Giles. The location between two hotels in downtown Nassau makes it easily accessible, while the piano bar adds to the overall ambiance.
name: JWB Prime Steak and Seafood
address: One Particular Harbour Nassau N.P, Nassau, Bahamas

name: On The Edge At The Fish Fry

excerpt: Small-batch rums & free tours at an 18th-century estate with resident birds & harbor views.
detail_description: John Watling's Distillery, located at the 1789 Buena Vista Estate in historic downtown Nassau, is a must-visit destination for rum enthusiasts and history buffs alike. The distillery offers complimentary tours where visitors can learn about the estate's rich history and its role in Nassau rum production. Guests can also sample some of the finest rums and spirits infused with Bahamian flavors during signature tastings at the Red Turtle Tavern.
name: John Watling's Distillery
address: Buena Vista Estate, 17 Delancy St, Nassau, Bahamas

excerpt: Traditional open-air market selling handwoven straw crafts, Bahamian souvenirs & tourist trinkets.
detail_description: Nassau Straw Market is a traditional open-air market in Nassau, Bahamas, offering a wide variety of handwoven straw crafts, Bahamian souvenirs, and tourist trinkets. Following a fire in 2001, the market was temporarily relocated but continues to thrive with dozens of vendors selling handmade wares such as straw hats, baskets, wood carvings, and seashell jewelry.
name: Nassau Straw Market

detail_description: Fish by José Andrés is a renowned fine-dining restaurant that focuses on serving exquisite Bahamian seafood. The restaurant is owned by the internationally acclaimed chef, José Andrés, who is known for his innovative culinary skills and humanitarian work. Fish offers a menu featuring delectable dishes such as crab cake sliders, whole grilled lobster, and mahi-mahi grilled over an open flame.
name: Fish
address: Paradise Beach Dr. Suite 15 Paradise Island N.P, Bahamas

detail_description: Twin Brothers is a popular restaurant in Nassau, known for its wide variety of Bahamian seafood dishes such as snapper, salmon, grouper, fried shrimp with potato salad, and lobster tail. Located in an area known as 'the fish fry,' it offers a range of seafood entrees including grouper, fried snapper, cracked lobster, salmon, shrimp and combination plates. The restaurant is also famous for its daiquiris.
name: Twin Brothers

detail_description: Humidor Churrascaria, located at the Graycliff Hotel in Downtown Nassau, offers a Brazilian-style dining experience. Guests can enjoy unlimited servings of expertly seasoned meats served tableside by gaucho waiters, along with a banquet-style buffet featuring an array of dishes including salads, vegetables, fresh fish, and Brazilian specialties. The restaurant's concept is inspired by the traditional Brazilian churrascaria where meats are grilled and served using large knives.
name: Humidor Churrascaria

detail_description: The Green Parrot - Harbour Front is a popular spot in Nassau, Bahamas, offering a laid-back atmosphere and stunning views of the Nassau Harbour and Paradise Island. It's conveniently located next to Bay Street Marina, making it an ideal stop for those arriving by private vessel. The bar is open seven days a week and welcomes all crowds, including furry friends. With its beach party vibe and shots menu, it's a great place to start your Nassau bar crawl.
name: The Green Parrot - Harbour Front

detail_description: The Cricket Club Restaurant & Pub is a great place to eat if you're a sports fan or just looking for a nice place to relax. They have TVs all over the place so you can watch your favorite games, and their British breakfasts are delicious.
name: Cricket Club Restaurant & Pub

detail_description: Tiki Bikini Hut is a vibrant bar located at Junkanoo Beach, near Downtown Nassau and the cruise line docks in The Bahamas. It offers an energetic atmosphere where visitors can savor drinks and food, including the popular conch fritters. The seating extends to the beach, providing stunning views of the ocean and cruise ships.
name: Tiki Bikini Hut

detail_description: Viola's Bar and Grill at Sunrise Beach Club and Villas is a beloved spot on Paradise Island, popular with both locals and tourists in the know. The menu offers a mix of American classics like burgers, pizza, sandwiches, and salads alongside Bahamian favorites such as curry chicken and conch fritters. Breakfast leans towards traditional American fare.
name: Viola's bar and grill

detail_description: If you're looking for a seafood restaurant with some serious mounds of food, Oh Andros is the place to go. The grilled conch here is especially delicious, and the staff is always friendly and welcoming. The only downside is that it can be quite busy, so make sure to book ahead.
name: Oh Andros

detail_description: If you're looking for a delicious and authentic caribbean meal, look no further than Curly's Restaurant and Bar in beautiful Arawak Cay. Enjoy delicious conch salad, fresh seafood, and steaks cooked to perfection - all at an affordable price! You'll never regret a trip to this popular spot!
name: Curly's Restaurant and Bar

detail_description: The Poop Deck, a well-established restaurant in Nassau for over 25 years, offers a blend of traditional Bahamian dishes and stunning views of the anchored Harbour boats and Paradise Island's lights. Guests can select their dinner from a variety of daily catches, including lane snapper, red snapper, hogfish, grouper, and spiny lobster prepared in various styles. Despite its unconventional name, the restaurant is renowned for its seafood selection and beachfront location.
name: Poop Deck

detail_description: At Olives, you'll find a unique, open-cuisine that celebrates the Mediterranean cuisine. The restaurant features three meals a day and late night dining options. Casual attire is recommended.
name: Olives
address: One Casino Drive Suite 18 Paradise Island N.P, Bahamas

detail_description: If you're dreaming of a tropical getaway, look no further than Jimmy Buffett's Margaritaville Bahamas. Nestled on the picturesque Junkanoo Beach in Downtown Nassau, this vibrant destination is perfect for both adventure seekers and those looking to unwind. Dive into fun at Fins Up Water Park, where you can ride the FlowRider simulator or take a thrilling leap from a ten-foot diving board.
name: Jimmy Buffett's Margaritaville Bahamas
address: 2 Marina Drive Paradise Island N.P, Bahamas

detail_description: Anthony's Seafood and Ribs is a vibrant and casual dining spot located near Nassau Harbour, offering affordable breakfast, lunch, and dinner options without compromising on quality. The menu features a wide variety of Bahamian and American dishes including popular items like baby back ribs with homemade barbecue sauce, seafood pasta, grouper, salmon, steaks, burgers, and mega-sized salads. The restaurant exudes an authentic Caribbean atmosphere with colorful decor and uplifting service.
name: Anthony's Seafood and Ribs

detail_description: Pizza Lab is a family-friendly dining spot located in front of The Showlakes. It offers a casual and lively atmosphere with large-screen televisions for sports enthusiasts and a spacious outdoor patio for al fresco dining. The restaurant serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner, featuring a wide variety of options including New York, Chicago, Sicilian, and Neapolitan pizza slices and whole pies. Additionally, they offer traditional Italian favorites such as pasta dishes along with an assortment of fresh desserts and gelatos.
name: Pizza Lab

detail_description: Owned and operated by a team of BBQ aficionados, Virgil's Real BBQ features some of the best barbecue in town. With a menu that includes both classic and unique dishes, the restaurant is perfect for all types of foodies. Whether you're goin for ribs or chicken, you're sure to find something that'll hit the spot at Virgil's!
name: Virgil's Real BBQ
address: One Casino Drive, Suite 27, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Murray's Deli is a delightful destination for anyone craving authentic New York-style deli cuisine, nestled within the picturesque Atlantis Paradise Island. With breathtaking views of the Atlantis Marina, this charming eatery offers a menu brimming with beloved classics such as challah French toast and bagels topped with lox. For lunch, indulge in their Coney Island-style kosher dogs served with savory beef sauce and crispy fries.
name: Murray's Deli
address: One Casino Drive, Suite 28, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Mosaic is a casual buffet restaurant with Mediterranean-influenced cuisine. It offers guests action cooking stations where dishes ranging from fresh fish to Churrasco are prepared on demand. Open for breakfast and dinner, dress code casual. Prices are high but the food is good.
name: Temp
address: One Casino Drive, Suite 24, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Latitudes, located at the Nassau Harbour Club, offers a waterfront dining experience with a diverse menu featuring both local and international cuisine. The restaurant provides stunning views of the marina, with outdoor and indoor seating options available. While some visitors have noted limited choices during happy hour, others praise the delicious food and excellent service. Despite being considered pricey by some, many find the quality of dishes to be worth it.
name: Latitudes

detail_description: Seafire Steakhouse, nestled within the vibrant Atlantis Resort on Paradise Island, is a must-visit for those seeking a modern dining experience infused with local flair. The restaurant boasts an inviting atmosphere characterized by high ceilings and striking tile work, complemented by an open display kitchen that adds to its contemporary charm. Diners can indulge in a menu that features Bahamian-inspired starters like creamy conch chowder and crab cakes alongside classic favorites such as Caesar salad and beef carpaccio.
name: Seafire Steakhouse
address: 3, One Casino Drive, Paradise Island, Bahamas

excerpt: Polished, long-standing hotel with a restaurant, a cigar bar & a wine cellar, plus outdoor pools.
detail_description: Nestled in downtown Nassau, the Graycliff Hotel offers a serene escape from the bustling city below. This historic hotel, originally built by a retired pirate in the 1700s, has been refurbished into a luxurious manor with traditional colonial decor. The rooms and cottages have hosted famous guests like Winston Churchill and Frank Sinatra. The hotel also features a renowned fine dining restaurant and an impressive wine cellar with over 200,000 bottles valued at $20 million.
name: Graycliff Hotel

detail_description: Nestled within the vibrant Baha Mar resort, The Swimming Pig Gastropub is a delightful culinary haven that pays homage to the famous swimming pigs of Exuma. This charming eatery offers a unique twist on traditional pub fare, making it a must-visit for food enthusiasts. Guests can indulge in mouthwatering dishes like the messy yet satisfying French dip au jus or savor their renowned burgers that have quickly made this spot a favorite among locals and visitors alike.
name: The Swimming Pig Gastropub

detail_description: Sugar Factory Baha Mar is a popular restaurant located in the Bahamas, known for its lavish dining room, legendary desserts, and premium cocktails. It's a great place to bring your kids for a unique dining experience while on a family vacation. The service and food are highly praised, with friendly staff offering plenty of recommendations. The presentation of the drinks and food is particularly noteworthy, making it an "Instagrammable" spot. The menu offers tasty and uniquely decorated foods, including vegetarian options like burgers.
name: Sugar Factory - Bahamas

detail_description: Blue Sail Bar & Grill, located in Sandyport, offers a chic and casual dining experience with a stunning view of the white sand beach and turquoise waters. The menu features Mediterranean-French fusion cuisine, including favorites like Yellow Fin Tuna Ceviche and Bahamian Conch Chowder. In addition to typical New Providence fare, the restaurant also offers dedicated sushi and wood-fired pizza menus.
name: Blue Sail Bar & Grill

detail_description: Poseidon’s Table at Atlantis Paradise Island offers a diverse buffet experience with options for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. The restaurant features a wide range of international cuisines, including healthy vegetarian choices and a Mexican Grill Station serving freshly-made tortillas. Families will appreciate the full breakfast buffet, Sunday brunch, and themed nights featuring Bahamian specialties and entertainment. While some may find the prices to be on the higher side, the variety of food options makes it suitable for everyone's taste buds.
name: Poseidon’s Table
address: One Casino Drive Suite 8, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: The Bahamian Club, located at Atlantis on Paradise Island, is a top restaurant in The Bahamas known for its traditional American steakhouse ambiance with a diverse selection of seafood and global dishes. The club exudes an upscale atmosphere with dark wood furnishings, plush chairs, and rich colors. It offers superb French and international cuisine in a setting reminiscent of the British Colonial era.
name: Bahamian Club
address: One Casino Drive Suite 6, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: Twisted Lime Sports Bar & Grill is a versatile spot that offers a laid-back atmosphere and Bahamas-style casual dining. Whether you're looking for a relaxing lunch with waterfront views or an animated night out, this place has got you covered. The menu features Bahamian-Mediterranean fusion dishes, including delicious fish options like grouper and snapper.
name: Twisted Lime Sports Bar & Grill
address: S Buckner Square Rd, Nassau, Bahamas

detail_description: Goldie’s Conch House in Nassau is a must-visit for those seeking an authentic taste of Bahamian cuisine and culture. This local favorite offers a variety of delicious seafood dishes, such as cracked conch, conch salad, and fried fish, all served in a warm and inviting setting. The restaurant's lively outdoor bar and live music performances add to the vibrant nightlife scene.
name: Goldie’s Conch House

detail_description: Fi'lia is an upscale Italian restaurant located at the Grand Hyatt Baha Mar in Nassau. The restaurant offers a peaceful and elegant ambiance, serving authentic Mediterranean cuisine and traditional Italian flavors. Known for its wood-grilled handmade bread, pasta, and pizza, Fi'lia also features tableside-tossed Caesar salad topped with Parmigiano and toasted garlic croutons.
name: Fi'lia

detail_description: Chop Stix is a gourmet restaurant that offers a fusion of contemporary Chinese cuisine with Pacific influences. The menu features traditional favorites like spicy soy chicken dumplings and pan-fried pork potstickers, as well as unique entrees such as wok-seared grouper and coconut mango curry chicken. The restaurant prides itself on using only the freshest, highest-quality ingredients to create delicious meals for guests to enjoy.
name: Chop Stix
address: One Casino Drive, Suite 14, Paradise Island, Bahamas

detail_description: The Bearded Clam Sports Bar & Restaurant, located in the heart of the International Arcade between Bay Street and the wharf, is a vibrant dining spot offering a wide array of seafood dishes centered around the queen conch, a renowned marine animal in The Bahamas. From conch balls to conch salad and burgers, this establishment caters to seafood enthusiasts. Additionally, as a sports bar, it's an ideal destination for those who enjoy both sports and drinks.
name: The Bearded Clam Sports Bar & Restaurant
